<div class="welcome-index">
<p class="welcome">Welcome to <span class="ubuntu">assemblyYard</span></p>
<p>You can search for <%= link_to "code", new_snippet_path %> by clicking on the link to the top right or <%= link_to "register", new_user_path %> to add and edit your own snippets of code.</p>
<p>When adding code it is important to :
<ul><li>Ensure you select the correct language - this will allow assemblyYard to display your code with the proper syntax highlighting.</li>
<li>Include search terms - these will allow you, and others, to find that code again.</li>
<li>Be reasonable. This is a friendly tool for nice people. Don't be a big meany!</li>
</ul>
</p>
<p>Thanks for visiting - love Sam </p>
</div>
<h1> Most Recent Code </h1>
<% @snippets.all.order("id desc").limit(5).each do |snippet|%>
<div class="index-snippet">
	<li><div class="name"><%= link_to snippet.name, snippet %></div></li>
	<pre class="language-<%= snippet.category.language %>" rel="<%= snippet.category.language %>"><code class="language-<%= snippet.category.language %>">
		<%= truncate(snippet.contents, length: 100) %>
	</code></pre>
	<li><div class="language"><div class="tags">Language: </div> <%= snippet.category.language %></div></li>
	<li><div class="search-terms"><div class="tags">Search Terms: </div> <%= snippet.search_terms %></div></li>
	<li><div class="user"><div class="tags">User: </div> <%= snippet.user.try(:user_name) %></div></li>
</div>
<% end %>
